Definition: concerned with work or important matters rather than play or trivialities
Example: a serious student of history; a serious attempt to learn to ski; gave me a serious look; a serious young man; are you serious or joking?; Don't be so serious!
Synonyms: noun, attribute, seriousness, FRIVOLOUS, concerned, with, work, or, important, matters, rather, than, play, trivialities, a, serious, student, of, history, attempt, to, learn, ski, gave, me, look, young, man, are, you, joking, Don, t, be, so
Category: adj.all
